                  </span></div><br><div class="comment">
                  <span class="c5a">&gt; The ransomware was built from NSA tools<p>I think that is bit disingenuous. The worm spreads through hole that was known to NSA and publicly disclosed and patched few months ago. That is hardly something I&#x27;d call &quot;NSA tool&quot;, they didn&#x27;t make the hole (best to our knowledge).<p>Sure, it would have been nicer if the discoverer would have been more forthcoming about the vulnerability, but that would have not really changed the fact that this exploitation happened well after the public disclosure and patch availability.<span>
